column10: Drivers speed through this stop sign with no regard to pedestrians. Sometimes even when seen, just swerve around them.

Cyclist ringing a loud bell speed though intersection, failing to stop or yield to other cars crossing though intersection. Cars had to slam on brakes to avoid very obnoxious and brazen attitude of as he weaved around cars, almost hitting me
This stop sign is primarily ignored by drivers. This is a very dangerous intersection.

Intersection traffic causes non stop honking with cars not following laws (full stop, speeding) or common courtesy. I live off the intersection and probably hear or view 2-5 near misses on a daily basis.
The stop signs on Blair Road at Pinetree Terrace are routinely and repeatedly run through by drivers on Blair Road.  About one in ten drivers actually stops at the stop signs.

An ongoing problem with cyclists who refuse to stop, or even slow down to yield to adults and children coming and going to school. They become very confrontational if this is brough to their attention. They are breaking the law and should be ticketed.

This is a two-way stop, but everyone assumes it's four-way. I'm nearly t-boned here almost daily as people barely stop or roll through the stop sign--they assume cross-traffic also has to stop (they don't). It would be much safer as a four-way stop.
